# coordinope

#### *verb* | co¬∑or¬∑di¬∑nope | \ k≈ç-Àà»Ør-d…ô-Àån≈çp \

## Definition

: to refrain from or reject attempts to align, synchronize, or work collaboratively with others

## Example Sentences

* After being asked to organize the office party for the third year in a row, she decided to coordinope and focus on her own projects instead.

* When the group text suggested another complicated weekend plan, he simply coordinoped and stayed home.

## Word History

First used in online communications (2020s) as a blend of coordinate (from Latin *co-* "together" + *ordinare* "to arrange") and *nope* (colloquial negative response used as a verb meaning "to reject"). Emerged in workplace contexts where individuals began asserting boundaries against excessive collaborative demands.

## Usage

Often used humorously in casual speech and writing to express a deliberate choice to opt out of coordination efforts that seem unnecessary or burdensome.
